---
layout: post
title:  "Some Motivational Quotes!"
date:   2015-01-28 22:01:31
categories: motivation
---

01
“If at first you don’t succeed, think how many people you’ve made happy.”
– H. Duane Black

02
“Success is a journey not a destination. The doing is usually more important than the outcome.”
– Arthur Ashe Jr

03
“There are no secrets to success. It is the result of preparation, hard work, and learning from failure.”
– Colin Powell

04
“I don’t know the key to success, but the key to failure is to try to please everyone.”
– Bill Cosby

05
“The power of imagination makes us infinite”
– John Muir

06
“Failure is only the opportunity to begin again more intelligently.”
– Henry Ford

07
“Nothing will ever be attempted if all possible objections must first be overcome.”
– Samuel Johnson

08
“You may be disappointed if you fail, but you are doomed if you don’t try.”
– Beverly Sills

09
“It is amazing what you can accomplish if you do not care who gets the credit.”
– Harry S. Truman

10
“If you care at all, you’ll get some results. If you care enough, you’ll get incredible results.”
– Jim Rohn

11
“Every artist was first an amateur.”
– Ralph Waldo Emerson

12
“The indispensable first step to getting the things you want out of life is this: decide what you want.”
– Ben Stein

13
“Obstacles don’t have to stop you. If you run into a wall, don’t turn around and give up. Figure out how to climb it, go through it, or work around it.”
– Michael Jordan

14
“Success is not the key to happiness. Happiness is the key to success. If you love what you are doing, you will be successful.”
– Herman Cain

15
“Many of life’s failures are people who did not realize how close they were to success when they gave up.”
– Thomas Edison

16
“Imagination is more important than knowledge.”
– Albert Einstein

17
“The difference between the impossible and the possible lies in a person’s determination.”
– Tommy Lasorda

18
“Only those who will risk going too far can possibly find out how far one can go.”
– T. S. Elliot

19
“The distance is nothing; it’s only the first step that is difficult.”
– Marquise du Deffand

20
“Nothing great was ever achieved without enthusiasm.”
– Ralph Waldo Emerson

21
“A great pleasure in life is doing what people say you cannot do.”
– Walter Gagehot

22
“If you really want to do something, you’ll find a way; if you don’t, you’ll find an excuse.”
– Frank Banks

23
“Some people want it to happen, some wish it would happen, others make it happen.”
– Michael Jordan

24
“Success is not permanent. The same is also true of failure.”
– Dell Crossword


